{A53: Old Indian Defence without Nf3} 1. d4 d6 2. c4 e5 3. d5 Be7 4. e4 Nf6 5.
Nc3 c6 6. Nf3 (6. f3 O-O 7. Be3 a5 8. Bd3 Na6 9. Nge2 Nd7 10. a3 Bg5 11. Bf2
Ndc5 12. Bc2 cxd5 13. Nxd5 a4 14. O-O Bd7 15. Nec3 Qa5 16. Be1 Qd8 17. Nxa4
Nxa4 18. Bxa4 Bxa4 19. Qxa4 Nc7 20. Qb3 Nxd5 {Razuvaev,Y (2560)-Vokac,M (2465)
Pardubice 1993 1/2-1/2 (59)}) 6... Qc7 $146 {Black has a cramped position} (
6... O-O 7. Be2 cxd5 (7... Na6 8. Nd2 Ne8 9. O-O Bg5 10. a3 c5 11. Bg4 Bxg4 12.
Qxg4 g6 13. Nf3 {1/2-1/2 (13) Meier,T (2200)-Benko,P (2440) Augsburg 1987}) 8.
cxd5 a6 (8... Nbd7 9. Qc2 a5 10. O-O Nc5 11. Be3 b6 12. Nd2 Ng4 13. Bxg4 Bxg4
14. a3 Nd7 15. f3 Bh5 16. b4 Qc7 17. Qb2 Rfc8 18. Rfc1 Qb7 19. Nb5 f5 20. Rxc8+
Rxc8 21. Rc1 axb4 22. axb4 Nf6 23. Nc4 {Ghinda,M (2455)-Perecz,L (2315)
Dortmund 1979 1/2-1/2}) 9. h3 Nbd7 10. Qc2 b5 11. O-O Nb6 12. a3 Bd7 13. Be3
Qb8 14. Nd2 Rc8 15. Rfc1 Bd8 16. Qb3 Be8 17. Rc2 Nbd7 {1/2-1/2 (17) Yermolenko,
V (2256)-Matjushin,G (2430) Shakhty 2015}) 7. Be2 a5 8. O-O Nbd7 9. Be3 h6 {
Consolidates g5} 10. Rc1 {White has an active position} Nf8 (10... Ng4 11. Bd2
$11) 11. Ne1 (11. Nd2 N6d7 $16) 11... c5 12. f4 (12. h4 N8d7 $14) 12... exf4
13. Bxf4 {White has a new backward pawn: e4. White has a very active position}
Ng6 14. Bg3 {White has an active position} Qd8 15. Nb5 {'the knight is the
knight!'} (15. Nd3 O-O $14) 15... Ra6 {Black has a cramped position} (15...
Nxe4 16. Qd3 Nxg3 17. Qxg3 $15) 16. Nd3 (16. Bf3 $142 $5 $14 {would keep White
alive}) 16... Nxe4 $15 17. Be1 {White has a king attack} O-O {Black castles
and improves king safety} 18. Bh5 {Black has a cramped position} Bg5 {Black
threatens to win material: Bg5xc1} 19. Rc2 Be3+ (19... Nf6 20. Bd2 $15) 20. Kh1
$11 {White has an active position} Nf6 21. Bxg6 (21. Re2 Nxh5 22. Rxe3 Nf6 $11)
21... fxg6 {Black has the pair of bishops.} (21... Bg4 22. Bxf7+ Rxf7 23. Qa1
$15) 22. Bh4 (22. h3 $5 $15 {is worth looking at}) 22... g5 $17 23. Bg3 (23.
Bf2 Bg4 24. Qe1 Bf4 $17) 23... Bg4 24. Qe1 Re8 25. Qa1 Ne4 26. Bf2 Nxf2+ (26...
Bd2 27. Nc3 Bxc3 28. bxc3 $19) 27. Nxf2 $17 Bd7 28. Re2 Bf4 (28... Bxb5 29.
cxb5 Ra8 30. Qe1 $17) 29. Rxe8+ Bxe8 (29... Qxe8 30. Nc7 Qh5 31. h3 $17) 30.
Nd3 (30. Qe1 $5 {looks like a viable alternative} Ra8 31. Nd3 Bxb5 32. Qe6+ Kh7
33. cxb5 $15) 30... Bxb5 $17 31. cxb5 Ra8 32. Nxf4 gxf4 33. Qd1 Qf6 34. Qd2 Re8
35. h3 b6 (35... Re3 36. Kg1 $19) 36. Rxf4 Re1+ (36... Qe5 $142 $5 $17) 37.
Qxe1 $11 Qxf4 1/2-1/2

