{[%mdl 8192] C90: Closed Ruy Lopez with 7...d6: Early deviations} 1. e4 e5 2.
Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 Bg4 9. h3
Bxf3 10. Qxf3 O-O 11. d3 Na5 (11... Rb8 12. Nd2 Nd7 13. Bd5 Na7 14. Nf1 Nb6 15.
Bb3 a5 16. a4 bxa4 17. Bxa4 Nxa4 18. Rxa4 Nc6 19. Ne3 Bg5 20. Nc4 Rb5 21. Bxg5
Qxg5 22. Rea1 Rfb8 23. g3 h5 24. h4 Qg4 25. Qxg4 hxg4 26. Kf1 {Sax,G (2524)
-Romanishin,O (2572) Bled 1999 1-0 (48)}) 12. Bc2 c5 13. Bg5 $146 (13. Nd2 Re8
(13... Ne8 14. Nf1 Bg5 15. Ne3 Nc6 16. g3 Ne7 17. a4 Bh6 18. Kg2 Nc7 19. Qg4
Qc8 20. f4 Kh8 21. Qxc8 Rfxc8 22. Ng4 Ng8 23. fxe5 Bxc1 24. Rexc1 h5 25. exd6
hxg4 26. dxc7 gxh3+ 27. Kxh3 bxa4 28. Rxa4 {Padmini,R (2454)-Htay,M (2286) Ho
Chi Minh City 2015 1-0 (50)}) (13... Nd7 14. Nf1 Bg5 {1/2-1/2 (14) Bellia,F 
(2399)-Salvador,R (2527) Milan 2010} 15. Ne3 Bxe3 16. Bxe3 Nc6 17. Rad1 Rc8 18.
Qg3 Qf6 19. f4 Qg6 20. Qf2 exf4 21. Bxf4 Qf6 22. Qg3 Nde5 23. Rf1 Qe6 24. Rf2
Qg6 25. Qxg6 hxg6 26. d4 cxd4 27. cxd4 Nc4 28. b3 g5 29. Bc1 Nb6 {Zaitsev,A 
(2402)-Khanov,V (2255) Tula 2005 1-0 (36)}) 14. Nf1 Nd7 15. Qg3 Kh8 16. Ne3 Bf8
17. Bd2 Nc6 18. Bb3 c4 19. dxc4 Nc5 20. Bc2 Rb8 21. cxb5 axb5 22. Nd5 Ne6 23.
a4 Qc8 24. b4 Ncd4 25. Bd1 Nc6 26. axb5 Rxb5 27. Be2 Rb8 {Dutreeuw,M (2410)
-Osman,G (2185) Moscow 1994 1-0 (60)}) 13... Nc6 {[%cal Yb5b4] Black plans b4}
14. Nd2 Rc8 15. Rad1 Qc7 16. Qe2 b4 {Black gets more space} (16... h6 17. Bh4
$11) 17. Nf3 a5 18. Bb3 h6 19. Bh4 (19. Bc1 bxc3 20. bxc3 a4 21. Bxa4 Qa5 22.
Bxc6 Rxc6 $16) 19... Nh7 20. Bxe7 Qxe7 21. d4 cxd4 22. cxd4 Nxd4 (22... Ng5 $5
{is interesting} 23. Nxg5 Qxg5 24. dxe5 dxe5 $11) 23. Nxd4 $16 exd4 24. Rxd4
Nf6 (24... Rc5 $5 $14) 25. Qa6 $16 Rc5 26. Qxd6 Qa7 (26... Re8 $5 $16) 27. e5
$18 Re8 $4 {shortens the misery for Black} (27... Ne8 28. Qd7 Qxd7 29. Rxd7 Nc7
$18) 28. Rf1 (28. Re3 $142 {secures the win} Rc1+ 29. Kh2 $18) 28... Rcxe5 $11
29. Rc4 Ne4 {Black threatens to win material: Ne4xd6} (29... R5e7 30. Ba4 Rf8
31. Rc2 $11) 30. Rc7 $14 Nxd6 31. Rxa7 Kf8 (31... R8e7 32. Ra8+ Kh7 33. Rd1 $14
) 32. Rd1 {White threatens to win material: Rd1xd6} (32. Rd7 a4 33. Bxa4 Rd5
$16) 32... Rd8 (32... Re1+ 33. Kh2 Rxd1 34. Bxd1 $11) 33. Rd5 (33. Kf1 f6 $16)
33... Rxd5 $14 34. Bxd5 f6 (34... Rc8 $142 $5 $14 {is noteworthy}) 35. Rxa5 $16
Nf5 36. Bb3 Nd4 37. Ra4 (37. Bc4 $5 $16) 37... Nxb3 $14 38. axb3 {A rook
endgame occured.} Rd4 (38... Rd1+ 39. Kh2 $14) 39. Kf1 $16 Ke7 40. Ke2 Ke6 41.
Ke3 Rh4 (41... Rd1 42. Rxb4 Rb1 43. Rb6+ Ke5 44. f4+ Kd5 45. h4 $16) 42. g3 {
White threatens to win material: g3xh4} (42. f4 $142 $5 $18) 42... Rxh3 $14 43.
Rxb4 {White has a new passed pawn: b3} Rh5 44. Re4+ Kf7 (44... Kd5 45. b4 $16)
45. b4 Rb5 46. Kd3 g5 $2 (46... Rb7 $142 $5 $16) 47. Kc4 $18 Rf5 $4 {leading
to a quick end} (47... Rb8 $142 48. b5 h5 $18) 48. Re2 h5 (48... g4 {is not
the saving move} 49. b5 Rg5 50. b6 $18) 49. b5 h4 (49... g4 {praying for a
miracle} 50. b6 Rg5 $18) 50. b6 h3 51. b7 h2 52. Re1 (52. b8=Q Re5 53. Rxe5
fxe5 54. Qh8 h1=Q 55. Qxh1 Kg7 56. Kd5 e4 57. Ke6 e3 58. Qb7+ Kh6 59. Kf6 Kh5
60. Qc8 exf2 61. Qh3#) 52... Rxf2 (52... Re5 53. Rh1 Re4+ 54. Kc5 Re8 55. Rxh2
Kg6 $18) 53. b8=Q Rc2+ (53... Kg6 {cannot undo what has already been done} 54.
Qe8+ Kh6 55. Re7 h1=Q 56. Qh8+ Kg6 57. Qxh1 Rf4+ 58. gxf4 Kf5 59. Qf3 Kg6 60.
f5+ Kh6 61. Qh3#) 54. Kb3 (54. Kb3 h1=Q 55. Qe8+ Kg7 56. Re7+ Kh6 57. Qh8+ Kg6
58. Qxh1 Rh2 59. Qxh2 f5 60. Qh7+ Kf6 61. Qf7#) 1-0

