{[%mdl 8192] D02: 1 d4 d5 2 Nf3 sidelines, including 2...Nf6 3 g3 and 2...Nf6
3 Bf4} 1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. c3 $146 {Controls b4} (4. Nf3 c5 5. Nbd2
Nbd7 6. c3 Be7 7. Ne5 O-O 8. Bd3 Nxe5 (8... a6 9. Qf3 cxd4 10. exd4 Nxe5 11.
dxe5 Nd7 12. Qh3 g6 13. O-O-O b5 14. Kb1 Nc5 15. Bc2 a5 16. Nf3 b4 17. c4 a4
18. Bd3 Qc7 19. Qh6 Nxd3 20. Rxd3 dxc4 21. Rd4 Re8 22. Bg5 Bf8 23. Qh4 {
Vujic,B (2357)-Karst,E (2317) Germany 2005 1-0 (39)}) 9. dxe5 Nd7 10. Qh5 g6
11. Qh6 f6 12. Bxg6 hxg6 13. Qxg6+ Kh8 14. h4 fxe5 15. Qh5+ Kg8 16. Bh6 Bf6 17.
Qg6+ Kh8 18. Bxf8 Nxf8 {Klaric,Z (2395)-Vul,A (2310) Kecskemet 1991 1-0 (31)})
4... c6 {Prevents intrusion on b5} 5. Nf3 Nbd7 6. Nbd2 c5 7. Bd3 c4 {Black
threatens to win material: c4xd3} 8. Be2 b5 9. b3 Qb6 (9... Nh5 10. O-O $11)
10. Rb1 $14 Qc6 11. Qc2 a5 12. bxc4 bxc4 13. O-O Ba6 {Black should quickly
conclude development.} 14. h3 {Covers g4} Be7 15. Ne5 Nxe5 16. Bxe5 O-O 17.
Bxf6 (17. Bf3 Ra7 $11) 17... Bxf6 $11 18. e4 {The typical lever} e5 (18... Rfe8
$142 $5 $11 {would allow Black to play on}) 19. exd5 $16 Qxd5 $2 (19... Qc7
$142 $5 20. Ne4 Be7 $16) 20. Bf3 $18 Qd7 (20... Qd8 21. Bxa8 Qxa8 22. Ne4 $18)
21. Bxa8 Rxa8 22. dxe5 (22. Qe4 $5 {seems even better} Rd8 23. dxe5 Be7 $18)
22... Bxe5 23. Nf3 Bf6 24. Rfd1 Qc7 (24... Qc6 25. Nd4 Qc5 26. Qb2 $18) 25. Re1
(25. Qf5 $5 h6 $18) 25... Bb7 26. Re3 g6 27. Rbe1 (27. Qb2 Bd5 $16) 27... Bc6 (
27... Kg7 28. Rd1 $16) 28. Nd4 Bd7 29. Qe4 Rd8 30. Qf3 Bg5 $4 {causes even
greater problems} (30... Kg7 $142 $16) 31. Re5 $18 Bd2 32. R1e2 Bc1 (32... f6
33. Qd5+ Be6 34. Qxe6+ Qf7 35. Qxf7+ Kxf7 36. Re7+ Kf8 $18) 33. Re7 Rf8 34. Qd5
Qc8 (34... Qf4 {doesn't change anything anymore} 35. Rxd7 Qf6 36. Rd6 $18) 35.
Qxd7 (35. Rxd7 Ba3 36. Nc6 Qxd7 37. Qxd7 h6 38. Re8 h5 39. Nd8 Be7 40. Qxe7
Rxe8 41. Qxe8+ Kg7 42. Qxf7+ Kh6 43. Qf8+ Kh7 44. Ne6 a4 45. Qg7#) 35... Qxd7
36. Rxd7 1-0

